{
  "text": "In our proofs we require one further condition on the a-priori measure µ 0 , which guarantees that exponential decay of connected spin-spin correlation functions holds at large values of |Re h|, assuming only that |Im h| ≤ const. × |Re h|. This will be proven with the help of a \"large-field cluster expansion\"; see Section 3. Large-field cluster expansions have been developed in [CITATION_1] in the context of two-dimensional continuum euclidian field theories. For reasons that will become apparent below, it is useful to parametrize the constant in the above inequality as const. = tan α, for α contained in (0, ). Namely, we assume that,",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "122356773"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "122356773": {
      "title": "The mass gap for the P (φ) 2 quantum field model with a strong external field",
      "abstract": "We consider theP(φ)2 hamiltonian whose interaction density is given by ::: ::: $$\\lambda P(\\phi (x)) + \\mu \\phi (x)^k $$ ::: ::: wherek is odd and 1≦k<degP. For sufficiently large μ we show that there is a gap in the energy spectrum. In addition we obtain new regions of analyticity in λ and μ for the Schwinger functions and the pressure."
    }
  }
